{"id":"428835640537739_504979376256698","type":"status","created_time":"2013-07-14T09:14:15+0000","message":"The constitution of the \u201cInternational Crimes Tribunal\u201d (ICT) is very worrying and the trial appears to be merely a process necessary to achieve foregone conclusions. The Tribunal members were appointed by the ruling Awami League party and count among its members individuals who were involved in earlier mock trials, in which Ghulam Azam and others were \u201cconvicted\u201d and effigies of them burnt to symbolise their execution"}